_meanings:
{@--1@} To instruct,
teach, explain, advise;  
{#yadyatprayogavizaye BAvikamupadiSyate mayA tasya…#} 
{#tattatpratyupadiSatIva me bAlA#} <ls>M. 1. 5</ls>;  
{#suKamupadiSyate parasya#} <ls>K. 156</ls> it is easy
to advise others; {#jYAnamupadiS#}  
<ls>Bg. 4. 34</ls>; <ls>R. 16. 43.</ls>

{@--2@} To point, 
indicate, refer to; {#guRaSezAmupadiSya#} 
{#BAminIM#} <ls>R. 8. 73</ls>; {#suvarRapuramArgamupadekzyati#}
<ls>K. 120</ls>, <ls n="K.">92</ls> point out or tell.

{@--4@} ({%a%}) To mention, specify,
tell; {#kiM kulenopadizwena SIlamevAtra kAraRaM#}
<ls>Mk. 9. 7</ls>; {#pfzodarAdIni yaTopadizwaM#}  
<ls>P. VI. 3. 109.</ls> ({%b%}) To inform, announce.

{@--5@} To
prescribe, settle, sanction, lay
down; {#na dvitIyaSca sADvInAM#} 
{#kvacidBartopadiSyate#} <ls>Ms. 5. 162</ls>, <ls n="Ms.">2. 190</ls>, <ls n="Ms.">3. 14</ls>,
<ls n="Ms. 3.">43</ls>; {#pfzodarAdIni yaTopadizwaM#}  
<ls>P. VI. 3. 109.</ls>
